# Build context for the GPU-free EVAL image (Containerfile / `podman build -t ivcbench .`).
# This image only needs the source, the deposited prediction bundles, and the analysis env, so the
# two heavy trees are excluded outright: build/ holds the multi-GB conda-pack tarballs for the
# training image, and data/ holds the raw single-cell datasets; neither is read when re-scoring the
# bundles. Keeping them out is what makes the eval build small (~200 MB context) and fast. The
# training image uses a separate ignore that re-includes build/train_envs/ (.dockerignore.train,
# wired in scripts/build_train_image.sh).
.git
.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
*.egg-info
reproduced_results.csv
out/
build/
data/
